  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "Where can I found highly experienced and qualified horse riding instructors in Melbourne?",
  "response": "If you're looking for highly experienced and qualified horse riding instructors in Melbourne, here are some reputable options where you can find skilled professionals:\n\n1. **Equestrian Centers and Clubs:**\n   - **Werribee Park Equestrian Centre**: Known for hosting major events and offering a range of lessons from beginner to advanced levels, their instructors are often highly qualified and experienced.\n   - **Yarrambat Equestrian Centre**: They provide a variety of programs and have experienced instructors who cater to different skill levels.\n   - **Boneo Park**: While primarily known for its eventing and show jumping facilities, Boneo Park also offers lessons with experienced instructors.\n\n2. **Riding Schools:**\n   - **Melbourne Polo Club**: Offers riding lessons with experienced instructors who can teach various aspects of horsemanship, including polo.\n   - **Lilydale Pony Club**: They have a range of instructors for different age groups and skill levels, and many of them are experienced and qualified.\n\n3. **Private Instructors:**\n   - You can find private instructors through word of mouth or online directories like Horse Agistment and Services Australia. Look for instructors with certifications such as EA (Equestrian Australia) accreditation, which is a good indicator of their qualifications and experience.\n\n4. **Equestrian Australia (EA) Website:**\n   - The EA website lists accredited coaches and instructors across Australia. You can filter by location to find instructors in Melbourne. EA-accredited instructors have undergone rigorous training and assessment, ensuring a high level of expertise.\n\n5. **Local Horse Riding Forums and Social Media Groups:**\n   - Joining local equestrian forums and social media groups can be a great way to get recommendations from other horse enthusiasts in Melbourne. People often share their experiences and recommend instructors they trust.\n\nWhen selecting an instructor, consider the following:\n- **Certifications and Qualifications:** Check if they are accredited by Equestrian Australia or similar bodies.\n- **Experience:** Look for instructors with extensive experience teaching riders at your skill level.\n- **References and Reviews:** Ask for references or look up reviews to gauge the instructor's reputation and effectiveness.\n- **Teaching Style:** Make sure their teaching style matches your learning preferences.\n\nBy considering these options and criteria, you should be able to find a highly experienced and qualified horse riding instructor in Melbourne.",
